Author: gcharang#6833
Content:
I'm not sure what specific problem with py you faced, but to properly run python3 scripts in my ubuntu16.04 that has default python2.7,
I have found that, installing a specific python3 version like 3.6 and  and referring to it explicitly when giving commands (running scripts or installing dependencies) works
Ex:
```
python3.6 -m pip install --user setuptools
python3.6 script.py
```
don't forget to change the first link of scripts from python3 to python3.6
